#chapter(19, "Good friends")[
  It was currently 7 PM in the Narumi household.

  Receiving the message that her parents would not make it in time for dinner,
  Mona had no choice other than to cook dinner for her and her sister again.
  Honestly, having to cook like this for three days straight is totally
  something out of the ordinary, especially considering that her father was
  always arriving home on time.

  When she entered the kitcheen, she caught her sister wearing an apron while
  happily saying "Let me help!". Of course, Mona could see nothing except
  impure thoughts within those eyes, and as a result, Sena would be kicked out
  of the kitchen entirely. After a bit of moping, Sena had no other choice other
  than sitting at the dining table and waiting for her sister to finish cooking.

  After a twenty-minute cooking session, everything was ready. Since it was a
  meal for just the two of them, there was nothing that fancy: just some boiled
  eggs and some stir-fried meat. And rice too, of course.

  Mona settled on the opposite side to the seat Sena was sitting at, while
  purposefully putting her schoolbag on the empty seat next to her. However, her
  attempts were futile, as her sister would instantly jumped to that seat after
  tugging that bag of hers away.

  "This is revenge for that morning, Mona!"

  After the torture session of her sister, both physically and mentally, Mona
  could finally have dinner in peace.

  "So you went on a karaoke session with friends today? How rare!"

  "It's not that big of a deal, sis." Mona replied nonchalantly, as she grabbed
  another piece of meat with her chopsticks.

  "The last day you also said you made friends, too!" Sena happily cheered,
  "Their names were Uto and Mikata, right?"

  "It's Uta and Mikoto!"

  "Oh right! No wonder why it was so hard to say their names."

  Mona, tired of her sister, returned her focus back to the meal. Even though
  the food was pretty bland today, it was still something she had not eaten for
  a long time. That alone made the food much better for her.

  Meanwhile, Sena did not like this meal a bit, but she was not in any position
  to complain. If she had cooked, not letting the kitchen on fire alone would be
  a miracle.

  So like any spoiled kid who could not finish their meals properly, Sena
  focused her attention to her smartphone.

  "Hmm, I've been looking at Mikoto-chan's Mitter replies... And she's been
  commenting quite regularly!"

  "I don't think a fashion model should go and stalk their fans..."

  "She's your friend, right? I wanted to make sure you're in good hands."

  "Who do you think you are? My mom?" Mona replied, "Also, don't you know that
  social media is where the fakest persona of people are displayed?"

  "I mean yeah..., but she's been commenting for a pretty long time, y'know."
  Sena scrolled through the replies section on the account allegedly belonged to
  Mikoto, "See, she's been doing this for at least five months, and this shows
  no signs of ending."

  Mona took a quick glance. _"Damn, every comment of her is different, she's
  really be taking the time, huh?"_

  "So, what do you think of her, then?"

  "Well- I think she's a pretty good person, I guess!"

  "What a generic remark." Mona put the final piece of rice into her mouth,
  before getting more rice from the rice cooker.

  "Okay, so Mikoto-chan is okay, I think it's time to see how Uta-chan really
  is."

  "You are not stopping, huh?"

  // suicidio numero
  "Let me see who is following Mikoto-chan..." Sena clicked on the "14
  following" button, trying to find Uta's profile.

  However, after a while of searching, she ended off with no potential
  candidates.

  "There's no one named Uta here..."

  "Well, Uta is pretty well-versed with this, so I don't think she would dox her
  real name on Mitter." Mona remarked.

  "Mona... do you have any social media of her?" Sena asked in despair.

  "I'm not a stalker like you, so no." Mona said with a mischievous tone, "Also,
  sis, if you don't eat, it will get cold, y'know."

  "Wait, Mona. Did you, perchance, have her on Mine?"

  "Yes, so what?"

  "Give me your phone NOW." Sena snatched the phone that was lying on the dining
  table. After unlocking it with the exact passcode Mona just changed one week
  earlier, she tapped on the Mine icon on Mona's homescreen.

  "Wait! How did you know the passcode?" Mona angrily questioned.

  // meta witch reference btw
  "A secret!" Sena pressed her finger on her mouth in a mischievous manner.
  Not letting a moment go by, she tapped on the Mine icon to see Uta's contact.
  "Let's see... Her handle is _\@alicefan621_, so maybe she has a similar handle
  on Mitter too... Ah- Found it!"

  "Really?" Mona could not hide her curiosity.

  Mona gazed at her phone screen. In front of her was a semi-professional
  Mitter account of no one other than her friend, Uta. There was even a sub
  account on her About Me section. The account has about 200 followers, much
  higher than average for a random high school account.

  Sena scrolled down to see selfies almost daily.

  "Hmm- This girl is really cute, so she must be nice!"

  "Hey, sis, did you really judge her by looks alone?"

  "No?" Sena paused, "But there is nothing here that shows her personality at
  all. I bet the sub account is the same, too!"

  Sena clicked on the sub account link to see a post that was posted 3 hours
  ago.

  // "Just got some ice cream today! It's not summer but whatevs! 🍨

  Underneath was a picture of a ice cream bar, freshly picked from a freezer.
  Though, a particular detail was bothering the two sisters' mind.

  "Did you see it, Mona?" Sena asked in a teasing manner.

  "See what, exactly?"

  "The flavor, I mean."

  "Well-, I can't see it well under the mist..."

  "If my dear sister can't read it, then I will gladly do it for you! It's
  C-h-o-c-o-m-i-n-t! Chocomint ice cream!"

  Mona remained in silence. Of course she knew which flavor it was by the color
  of the packaging, but she was trying to avoid having to name this "disgusting"
  flavor.

  "Mona... It seems even your friends are betraying you, dear sister."

  "She just lost a bet, that's it!"

  "Really? Explain this, then."

  Sena pointed to a self-reply of Uta right under the post,
  saying "Nothing beats a chocomint ice-cream after school."

  "That was also a part of the bet too!"

  "Mona... Escaping from reality is not a good thing." Sena put her hand onto
  one of Mona's shoulders, "I will help you cope with the reality that chocomint
  is the peak ice cream flavor."

  "I will keep enjoying strawberry ice cream, thanks."

  The two sisters kept bickering with each other, until Sena accidentally swiped
  the screen down to see a previous post from the Mitter account.

  Sena instinctively read its content, before her face went pale. Seeing her
  sister's reaction made Mona intrigued and she proceeded with reading the post.
  Once her eyes scanned a certain keywords, they both lit up. Sena tried to turn
  off the screen, but it was a little too late.

  "Sis... You don't have to hide it like that... I saw the word." Mona, now
  imitating Sena's previous intimidating voice, "N-a-t-t-o."

  "NO! Even the thought of it disgusted me." Sena screamed in genuine horror.

  "Uta really had a W food taste. Meanwhile a certain someone could not
  even bare the thought of peak food." Mona smirked, before lightly muttered
  "Except for her ice cream, that is."

  "It's probably her parents who forced her to eat natto from a young age! Poor
  girls, being detoxicated by your own parents..."

  "Now your turn to make a shitty excuse..." Mona sighed.

  "Anyway, these food discussions show nothing about her personality, so Mona,
  can you tell me a bit about Uta-chan? And Mikoto-chan too, if possible?"
  Sena asked in a nice voice, seemingly asking her sister to unconditionally
  forget the previous topic.

  "What a poor attempt of changing the subject... Anyways, I'm done with dinner
  now."

  "Wait, Mona, just answer the question, please. Your sister wanted to know if
  you are hanging with good friends or not."

  "Haizz- Mikoto's the kind of energetic girl who's like the protagonist of a
  generic CGDCT anime. Well actually since she's in a sports club it would be
  more like a girls sports anime, like the TakaYori show this season..."

  "I guess I can picture that..." Sena replied.

  "About Uta... Well, she doesn't talk much, but I felt like she really cares
  about the people around her. Today she just briefly looked at me and already
  knew that it's my first time doing karaoke, after all. And she was the one
  clapping loudest when I'm singing, too."

  Mona naturally beamed a genuine smile while talking about Uta. Seeing that
  heartwarming smile also made her sister smile, too.

  "Sound like a good friend, isn't she?"

  "Uhm." Mona replied in a gentle tone.

  "Well, if so, then I'm rest assured."

  Mona would then go to her favorite place, the sofa in front of the family TV
  to watch her evening idol TV shows. Sena stayed at the dining table to finish
  her meals, before taking the dishes to the sink to be cleaned.

  It was yet another peaceful evening of the two sisters.
]
